        <br />
        <div class="paragraphs">
            <h6 class="company-histoy">
                in 1997, Theatre Vertigo was founded by Paul Floding. Nonelle Pettit and Jeff <br />
                Meyers.
                Since then, Theatre vertigo has performed in numerous spaces including <br /> the Russell Street theatre,
                The Electric Company, theaterTheotrel, and the <br /> ShoeBox Theater.
            </h6>

            <h6 class="middle-paragraph">
                From 2003 to 2014, Theatre Vertigo produced Anonymous Theatre as a summer <br />
                fundraiser in collaboration with the Anonymous Theatre Company. Other past <br />
                collaborations include defunkt theatre. Stark Raving Theater, and Tears of Joy <br /> Theatre.
            </h6>

            <h6 class="third-paragraph">
                Theatre Vertigo has worked on world premieres inclusing Faust.Us by Joseph Fisher. <br />
                99 Ways to Fuck a Swan by Kim Rosenstock, and the End of Sex by Craig Jessen
            </h6>

            <h6 class="fourth-paragraph">In 2016, Theatre Vertigo produced its first offically commissioned work from a <br /> playwright, I want to Destroy You, by Rob Handel</h6>
            <br />
            <br />
        </div>
